[1] VEE - Belize: OIE immediate notification
Date: Mon 31 Aug 2009
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2009; 22(36) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Venezuelan equine encephalomyelitis, Belize
-------------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 31 Aug 2009 from Dr Victor
Gongora, Director of Animal Health, Animal Health Department, Belize
Agricultural Health Authority (BAHA), Belmopan, Belize

Summary
Epidemiology
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 14 Aug 2009
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 31 Aug 2009
Report date: 31 Aug 2009
Date submitted to OIE: 31 Aug 2009
Reason for notification: unexpected increase in morbidity or
mortality of a listed disease
Summary description: cases reported have been more than what is
normally expected and the distribution is greater.
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Venezuelan equine encephalomyelitis virus
This event pertains to the whole country
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors

Epidemiological comments: Belize has reported an increase in
mosquitoes and the Ministry of Health has stepped up vector control
activities. One equine case in the Cayo District was also confirmed
as eastern equine encephalomyelitis (17 Jul 2009). One isolated case
in Belize District in January 2009, another isolated case in Stann
Creek in April 2009 then surge in Cayo in July-August. The National
Veterinary Services Laboratory (NVSL) has confirmed cases in the 3
districts.

Increased distribution
The areas and species that have recently become affected by the
disease include Stann Creek (Equidae); Belize (Equidae), and Cayo
(Equidae).

Disease impact
Increased / Total / Species / Change
Incidence / Stann Creek / Equidae / 0 to 1
Incidence / Cayo / Equidae / 1 to 3
Incidence / Belize / Equidae / 0 to 1

Control measures
Measures applied:
- control of arthropods
- vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Stann Creek / Equidae / 19 / ranch horses
Cayo / Equidae / 224 / 4 villages have reported cases
Belize / Equidae / 19 / horses belong to a resort
- no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied:
- control of wildlife reservoirs
- movement control inside the country

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National Veterinary Services Laboratory
(OIE's reference laboratory)
Species: Equidae
Test: IgM-capture ELISA
Test date: 31 Aug 2009
Result: positive

Future reporting: the event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports
will be submitted.

--
